They are tempted by the prospect of manipulating virtual objects in the air with bare hands, by creating open virtual spaces.
Can you tell us in a few words what your research team is doing?
We are working on the interaction between man and machine and at the same time we are trying to broaden the boundaries of this interaction.
Humanity as a whole has remained for the moment on flat screen pixels and sometimes on the touchscreen.
We want to look 5 to 10 years ahead and guess the radical changes that will occur with this interaction.
