Significant differences in labour price (wages) generate pressure on prices.
It is appropriate to put under this term the following meaning: a producer strives by importing goods sold low to resist economic competition by "making more expensive" the competitor's price, in order to remove a greater share of the market and thus increase his own profits.
On a large scale, this means for most entrepreneurs: either transfer production abroad, buy at low prices, or disappear.The result is significant unemployment in countries where labor prices are high compared to other economies.
