In contrast, many philosophers and writers talk about a link between boredom and creativity, said Professor Vodanovich, who has been studying the problem for more than two decades.
“Dullness is the way the brain has found to let you know you should do something else,” said Gary Marcus, a professor of psychology at the New York University.
But the brain doesn’t always know what is the most appropriate thing to do.
