He proposes to reorient this inefficient distribution; that condoms not only be sold at the counter, but that they be found in the public toilets and in the places that young people attend.
It is not about encouraging promiscuity.
Nor is it about paying them for the girls and the motel, as Governor Emilio González replied when asked if there would be a distribution of condoms within his administration.
"It's not how sexuality works, it's best to provide condoms to people who are already sexually active," he said.
Events in Jalisco
